    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 16 Sep 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I will take the position of Lecturer (≈ Assistant Professor) in Natural Language Processing at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edinburghnlp.inf.ed.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Edinburgh&lt;/a&gt; from August 2022. &lt;strong&gt;I am currently recruiting students!&lt;/strong&gt; Apply for a &lt;em&gt;fully funded&lt;/em&gt; 4-year PhD with integrated study at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edin.ac/cdt-in-nlp&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;NLP Centre for Doctoral Training&lt;/a&gt; or for a &lt;em&gt;fully funded&lt;/em&gt; 3-year PhD at the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.ed.ac.uk/informatics/postgraduate/research-degrees/phd&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Istitute for Language, Cognition and Computation (ILCC)&lt;/a&gt;. The deadline for international / EU applicants is 26 November 2021.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am currently a postdoctoral fellow in computer science at &lt;a href=&#34;https://mila.quebec/en/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Mila - Quebec AI Institute&lt;/a&gt; in Montreal and an affiliated researcher at the University of Cambridge. In 2020, I obtained a PhD in computational linguistics from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cam.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Cambridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.joh.cam.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;St John&amp;rsquo;s College&lt;/a&gt;. I am also a frequent collaborator of &lt;a href=&#34;https://rycolab.github.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Ryan Cotterell&amp;rsquo;s lab&lt;/a&gt; at ETH Zürich. Previously, I interned as AI/ML researcher at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.apple.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Apple&lt;/a&gt; in Cupertino.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My ultimate goal is to reconcile how machines learn and use natural language with the way humans do. This is a source of inspiration to address some of the open challenges in developing technology for hundreds of the world&amp;rsquo;s languages, which originate from their scarcity of annotated data and their typological variation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sample efficiency&lt;/strong&gt;, learning from just a few examples by virtue of inductive biases;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;modularity&lt;/strong&gt;, disentangling different facets of knowledge and recombining them in original ways in order to better generalise to novel domains;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;robustness&lt;/strong&gt; in transferring knowledge between differently distributed domains;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;grounding&lt;/strong&gt; language learning and use in perception and action;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My research earned a &lt;a href=&#34;https://ai.google/research/outreach/faculty-research-awards/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Google Research Faculty Award&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mmll.cam.ac.uk/news/prof-anna-korhonens-project-enabling-multilingual-conversational-ai-awarded-erc-proof-concept&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;ERC Proof of Concept grant&lt;/a&gt;. I received 2 Best Paper Awards at &lt;a href=&#34;https://2021.emnlp.org/blog/2021-10-29-best-paper-awards/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;EMNLP 2021&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.aclweb.org/anthology/W19-4310.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;RepL4NLP 2019&lt;/a&gt;. I had the oppotunity to discuss my research in many &lt;a href=&#34;talks&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;invited talks&lt;/a&gt;. Finally, I am a board member of &lt;a href=&#34;https://sigtyp.github.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;SIGTYP&lt;/a&gt;, the ACL special interest group for computational typology, and a member of the European Lab for Learning and Intelligent Systems (&lt;a href=&#34;https://ellis.eu/members&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;ELLIS&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
